        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:38PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ruidoso Downs, or 5 miles southeast of Ruidoso, moving northwest at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ruidoso, Lincoln, Ruidoso Downs, Capitan, Fort Stanton, Glencoe,
Smokey Bear Historical Park, Alto, Lincoln State Monument and
Angus.

This includes Highway 380 between Mile Markers 81 and 98.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
